                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>President Truman on August 1 sent a letter to Sam Rayburn, Speaker of the House
                    of Representatives, transmitting a supplemental estimate of appropriation for
                    the year 1951 of $4 billion to provide military assistance to foreign nations.
                    For text of the letter, see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>,
                    August 14, 1950, page 247.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
